with out Indexing

* It checks every document in the collection one by one.
* Queries are slower, especially as the collection grows.
* CPU and memory usage increase.
* Multiple matching documents cause more unnecessary scans.
* totalDocsExamined equals almost the whole collection even if only a few documents match.

Types of Indexing

Single-Field Index
Index on a single field.
db.collection.createIndex({ fieldName: 1 })  // 1 â†’ ascending
db.collection.createIndex({ fieldName: -1 }) // -1 â†’ descending

Compound Index
Index on multiple fields (order matters).
db.collection.createIndex({ field1: 1, field2: -1 })
Query benefits if it matches the prefix fields of the index.

Unique Index
Prevents duplicate values.
db.collection.createIndex({ email: 1 }, { unique: true })

Multikey Index
For array fields, indexes each element.
db.collection.createIndex({ tags: 1 })

Text Index
For searching string content.
db.collection.createIndex({ title: "text", description: "text" })

Query example:
db.collection.find({ $text: { $search: "mongodb" } })




What is Schema Designing?

Schema Designing is the process of planning and defining the structure of data in a databaseâ€”that is, what fields exist, their data types, relationships, constraints, and indexesâ€”before storing data.

In simple words:

Schema design decides how your data is organized, stored, and accessed efficiently.

ðŸ”¹ Why Schema Designing is Important

Good schema design helps to:

Store data in a clean and consistent way

Avoid data duplication

Improve query performance

Make the application scalable and maintainable

Support security and data integrity
db.createCollection("faculty", {
  validator: {
    $jsonSchema: {
      bsonType: "object",
      required: ["empId", "name", "role"],
      properties: {
        empId: {
          bsonType: "string",
          description: "Employee ID must be string and is required"
        },
        name: {
          bsonType: "string",
          description: "Name must be string"
        },
        role: {
          bsonType: "string",
          description: "Role must be string"
        },
        department: {
          bsonType: "string"
        },
        age: {
          bsonType: "int",
          minimum: 21
        },
        email: {
          bsonType: "string"
        },
        createdAt: {
          bsonType: "date"
        }
      }
    }
  }
})

db.faculty.createIndex({ email: 1 }, { unique: true })


